## Example Usage

### Minimal database

```terraform
data "duplocloud_tenant" "tenant" {
  name = "dev"
}

resource "duplocloud_aws_glue_database" "analytics" {
  tenant_id = data.duplocloud_tenant.tenant.id
  name      = "analytics"
}
```

### Database with description and parameters

```terraform
resource "duplocloud_aws_glue_database" "analytics" {
  tenant_id = data.duplocloud_tenant.tenant.id
  name      = "analytics"
  body_json = jsonencode({
    Description = "Analytics tables for the data team"
    LocationUri = "s3://my-bucket/analytics/"
    Parameters = {
      classification = "csv"
    }
  })
}
```

## body_json

The `body_json` attribute accepts any AWS Glue `DatabaseInput` fields documented at
[CreateDatabase](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/glue/latest/webapi/API_CreateDatabase.html).
Do not include `Name` — it is set by the provider from the `name` attribute.
Computed fields returned by AWS (such as `CreateTime`, `CatalogId`) are kept in
state but do not trigger a diff unless your configuration explicitly sets them.

## Import

```shell
terraform import duplocloud_aws_glue_database.analytics <TENANT_ID>/<DATABASE_NAME>
```

